reviewText: Unfortunately I watched his second stand up performance first and found this one a little more retro. Although enjoyable, I have to admit watching that much orange in motion is eye catching! LOL
Title: Ralphie May: Austin-tatious

reviewText: I think no matter what your humor you're into you can appreciate this performance. This is my favorite of his that I've seen. He's a lot less dynamic than other comedians in that he doesn't (or can't) work the stage the way I really like but his jokes hit so hard that becomes irrelevant. Whether you're a collector of stand-up or just need some entertainment for a nice Saturday afternoon, this is it.
Title: Ralphie May: Austin-tatious

reviewText: Ralphie May is a talented comedian.  Keeps you laughing, so more than one viewing is necessary to catch the parts you didn't hear the first time.

reviewText: I saw Ralphie May on last comic standing and thought he was great. This DVD only has a few good laughs. It's mostly dirty, which I wouldn't mind if the jokes were at least funny, but they're not.

reviewText: Ralphie May says anything and everything about everybody in his stand up. If you do not like crude or are sensitive about race this isn't for you. I laughed my butt off. Very funny, thanks for the laughs Ralphie.
